The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm that efficiently handles high-dimensional tensor data, which is a common problem in areas such as computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of support vector machines, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant. Finally, the numerical experiments involve solving optimization problems, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
